		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Best Warrior Race Out There<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Dec 13th 5:33 AM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=9766856055728&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=9766856055728&num=7&page=&post=1&replyto=9766856055728"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=9766856055728></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=8127"><span id=>Praxxis</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>1 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Praxxis&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>If you want to play a warrior, go for the Iksar. Reasons:<br><br>1) High agility, and Swimming at 100 to begin with.<br><br>2) Forage, a very useful skill.<br><br>3) Beginning Iksar warriors get a pike that usually hits for about 12-16 damage...and that's starting off!<br><br>4) Doing the quest for Curscale Armor for Klok Mugruk not only gets you a full set of not bad armor for early levels, but also gets you to level 5 before you know it.<br><br>I've only played one warrior, and it's Iksar, and if given the chance, I don't think I'd want to play any other race. They are the best, without a doubt. There is that whole pesky KoS to everything problem, but there's nothing you need that you can't find in Kunark. If you wanted, you could easily reach lvl 30 and never step foot off the continent. Sure, it would be dull, but you take what you can get. Well, there's my 2cp, now let's get on with the bashing of my comment!!!</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Praxxis<br>Warrior and Officer of<br>The Knights Discordia<br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >7 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Dec 13th 8:59 AM2000 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=9766856055728&num=7&page=&post=1&replyto=97669794723503"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=97669794723503></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Come on man, Iksar?<br>Ok ok, maybe levels 1-5 or 10 are easier, BUT...<br><br>1) The rest of their stats are okay at best.<br>Do we really swim that much?<br><br>2) Forage? ok, nice at times, but a pain in the @$$ as far as I'm concerned... who wants to run around dropping drood poop everywhere?<br><br>3) Gonna use that pike when you're level 50?<br><br>4) Iksar CAN'T wear plate armor!!! NO Crafted, NO Indicolite, NO Cobalt EVER!<br><br>You neglected to mention the best thing about the Iksar... their natural regeneration, which is awesome at low levels, but not much good when you've got 3000 HPs and a cleric at your back.<br><br>And as far as KoS is concerned it can be fixed but why not spend that time leveling instead?<br><br>There's alot of different reasons to play each race of warrior, but I see a few that far outweigh the Iksar.<br><br>Humans get no exp penalty for race. They start in Freeport, which one most servers is THE place to buy cheap gear as well as a good place to farm bone chips, bat wings, etc. to sell to the high levels running thru.<br><br>Wood Elves look the best in armor. High Dex and Agi which is good for skills and proccing, and alot of the good warrior gear has Str on it.<br><br>Dwarves have good stats in Str and Sta, and look alright in game IMO. And, never need a shrink.<br><br>BUT, none of those races can Slam. I NEVER use kick. Kick takes more Stamina to use, does only a little more damage and has no chance to stun a mob. (Slam will stun a running mob) So, let's move on...<br><br>Barbarians start with higher Str than the smaller races. Which is good both at all levels. Strength drastically affects your Attack Value which means you do more damage and hit more often (making skills a little less difficult to raise). But, they start in the middle of nowhere giving them less of a chance to have good gear at low level.<br><br>Trolls have good stats and natural regen, which I covered before under the Iksar P. They require a shrink alot more often than Barbs since they're a bit larger. They're also KoS in many places, and still pretty far from civilization. They're ugly as sin and stand around scratching their @$$es too. P<br><br>Ogres have the highest starting Str and Sta. They also seem to have a big hit point bonus, which is nice at all levels. They cannot be stunned while facing a mob! They need shrinks ALOT, but that is fairly easily overcome especially since the advent of the 10 charge potions. They also scratch, but depending on how you play your character and your personality they can be fun.<br><br>Were I to start back at level 1 I would have to pick the Ogre. The hit point bonus, high Str and that stun thing make up for their being KoS, and kinda isolated starting point.<br><br>Zubekhan<br>Wolf of the North<br>Veteran of 53 campaigns<br>Saryrn</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
